### CodeForge Auth API — Manual test file
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or IntelliJ HTTP Client
### Set @token after login/register response

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@token = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### ── Register ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "devuser",
  "email": "dev@example.com",
  "password": "DevPass1"
}

### ── Login ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@example.com",
  "password": "DevPass1"
}

### ── Get current user ────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ── Refresh token ───────────────────────────────────────────────
### (Cookie is sent automatically by REST client if using same session)

POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh

### ── Logout ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

DELETE {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ── Logout all devices ──────────────────────────────────────────

DELETE {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout-all
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ── Health check ────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### ── Error cases ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Weak password (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "weakuser",
  "email": "weak@example.com",
  "password": "password"
}

### Wrong credentials (should return 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword1"
}

### Missing auth header (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
